Even though the post election period is normally not a time to change governments, certainly this coup wasn’t allowed to block the democratic process, ultimately led to the election of President Francoise Bozize, who remained in power until the coup of March 23rd, 2013.

A video shows men dressed in military gear burning tyres in Bangui. A 2-minute clip, it does not explain the reasons of the burning or the time and place.

Unidentified People in the Burkina Faso capital of Ouagadougou are burning a tree on the 18th of April, 2019 in front of police forces, so apparently on the 17th of April the opposition protesters got a new tactic to cause damages without being chased. The following day, police used teargas and a water cannon to disperse the protesters. That was until it was particularly night-shots that were showing up all over social media.

Watch a video of Charles Taylor on trial, apologizing for all damages he has caused to people of Sierra Leone in the past.
